        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Καὶ λατρεύσουσί μοι ἐν τῷ τόπῳ τούτῳ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 3:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", LXX., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "καὶ λατρεύσετε τῷ Θεῷ ἐν τῷ ὄρει τούτῳ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". These words spoken to him Moses records of the place, Horeb, not excluding the land of Canaan: Ibid. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 7:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". For if service (worship) on Horeb was a sign of Moses’ mission, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 3:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", much more service in the land of Canaan was a sign. Therefore Stephen has woven together the oracles given to Abraham and Moses, in this sense; “They shall go forth from the land of bondage (this was said to both Abraham and Moses), and shall come to Horeb, and shall serve the Lord in this place; and shall come thence into the land of Canaan, and shall serve the Lord.” In thus weaving together these things, he shows in a strong way, (1) that what was said to Moses as to the worship of Israel towards GOD, was already in the time of Abraham divinely intended and meant: (2) that they were taught in Horeb to serve GOD for this purpose, that they might worship Him perpetually in the land of Canaan, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 7:44",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " : (3) that the worship in Horeb was very much curtailed by the people [owing to their idolatry of the calf], ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 7:40-41",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and was rather rendered at length when they entered into the land of Canaan; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 7:45",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “They shall serve Me,” is the expression used; they shall not, as previously, serve the Egyptians; they shall serve in freedom, as Priests.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
